                     <title xml:lang="en">A collection of the ghazals of Sa'ib.</title>
                     <note>F1a: note of ownership of Muhammad Hasib, dated 1[0?]95 (1683-4?). Last folio, recto: obscure impression of small rectangular seal. Last folio, verso: Two impressions of a large oval seal: Fadlallah talib-i faid-i amjad?, dated 1141 (1728-9) and regnal year 14. Inside front cover: armorial bookplate of Gordon of Buthlaw. Ruled headings and dividing panels. Panel of illumination over beginning of text.</note>
                     <incipit>Dar qulzum-i may hubab ast del-i ma</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, ii, pp. 693-5.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe No 1606 ff.</bibl>
                        <bibl>General Gordon's bequest of books and Turkish, Perian and Arabic manuscripts is mentioned, without details in the donations register under November 6 1841. The bequest is mentioned in J.R.A.S., vii, 1843, Annual Report, p. x, and the manuscripts are briefly listed in the Proceedings, pp. xxx-xxxi.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
